The best way to install StilleBot on OS X is to use Homebrew. Start by opening a Terminal and typing:
$ brew install pike
You may need to additionally install XQuartz:
http://xquartz.macosforge.org/
Once Pike is installed, you should be able to download StilleBot from this link,
or clone the repository using git:
https://github.com/StilleBot/Gypsum/archive/master.zip
Extract this to a convenient directory, then run stillebot.pike using Pike.
